- Yeah, we did.

07:10.255 --> 07:12.649
- The hole Milo dug for
himself just got deeper.

07:12.780 --> 07:15.391
- Yeah, I think he
might've dug a hole for us.

07:15.522 --> 07:18.307
- Mike, if you fall in it,

07:18.438 --> 07:22.050
don't fucking drag us
down there with you.

07:22.180 --> 07:25.488
- With regards to Mr. Sunter,
I know where we stand.

07:25.619 --> 07:27.142
Where do you stand?

07:27.272 --> 07:30.493
- Look, I don't see motive.

07:30.624 --> 07:32.974
Don't see opportunity, at least.

07:33.104 --> 07:34.845
Not directly.

07:34.976 --> 07:38.632
But the circumstantial
evidence is pretty damning.

07:38.762 --> 07:40.547
It's his land.

07:40.677 --> 07:41.983
He threatened Mike to move
something from this property.

07:42.113 --> 07:44.289
And the circumstantial evidence
points to him committing

07:44.420 --> 07:46.248
multiple felonies to
force Mike to do it.

07:46.378 --> 07:50.121
I don't see a prosecutable
case from this.

07:52.384 --> 07:56.519
But...

07:56.650 --> 07:59.783
I mean...

07:59.914 --> 08:03.831
Let me get the bodies
to the morgue, Evelyn.

08:03.961 --> 08:05.354
Let me find you something
you can work with.

08:05.485 --> 08:07.443
- I want him moved to county.

08:07.574 --> 08:10.533
I want to spin his head a bit.

08:10.664 --> 08:14.102
Then I want that son of a bitch
in front of a judge by Monday.

08:14.232 --> 08:15.712
- Ian. You want this?

08:15.843 --> 08:17.409
- Fuck no, I don't want it.

08:17.540 --> 08:19.673
- Well, it's yours anyway.
Take Kyle and Stevie.

08:22.284 --> 08:25.548
Rush jobs never hold
up in court, Evelyn.

08:25.679 --> 08:27.637
Let's do this right
so it sticks.

08:27.768 --> 08:30.031
- Let's do this right.
Let's do it fast.

08:31.772 --> 08:33.382
Walk with me, please?

08:33.513 --> 08:35.036
- Yeah.

08:37.647 --> 08:39.431
- Look, I don't believe in luck.

08:39.562 --> 08:42.870
And if I did, I would not
believe that you had any.

08:43.000 --> 08:46.264
- I can't argue with you there.
- Yeah, so,

08:46.395 --> 08:49.659
how did you stumble
upon the crime of the decade?

08:51.661 --> 08:55.360
- He wanted me to.

08:55.491 --> 08:57.058
- Why would he want that, Mike?

08:57.188 --> 08:59.016
- I don't know.

08:59.147 --> 09:01.802
- Well, you better figure it
out before someone else does.

09:01.932 --> 09:04.979
And when you do, you
come straight to me,

09:05.109 --> 09:08.417
because you know what
you look like right now?

09:08.548 --> 09:11.159
You look like a
big fucking patsy.

09:11.289 --> 09:12.900
- I'm thinking the same thing.

09:13.030 --> 09:20.168
- ♪

09:23.084 --> 09:28.263
