I ordered you a filet.

09:35.705 --> 09:39.361
- ♪

09:39.491 --> 09:44.540
- [crashing, clanking]

09:46.150 --> 09:48.675
- Mike, Mike, Mike!
Stop with the gangster shit!

09:48.805 --> 09:51.068
- Yeah.

09:51.199 --> 09:52.896
Send me on a gangster errand,

09:53.027 --> 09:55.246
gangster shit's what
you're gonna get, okay?

09:55.377 --> 09:57.248
- Did you find the case?
- The metal case, right?

09:57.379 --> 09:58.728
- Yeah.
- Yeah, yeah. I found it.

09:58.859 --> 10:01.296
You know what's in it?
Twenty-six fucking bodies

10:01.426 --> 10:03.472
wrapped in a fucking cocoon,
Paul!

10:03.603 --> 10:05.474
- You found what?
- Yeah, yeah.

10:05.605 --> 10:06.867
No, I got a lot of problems.

10:06.997 --> 10:08.999
But stuttering is
not fucking one of 'em!

10:09.130 --> 10:12.394
- Bodies?
- Yeah! I'm surprised too.

10:12.524 --> 10:13.917
- Mike, no, no, no, no, no.

10:14.048 --> 10:15.310
That's not what you
were supposed to find.

10:15.440 --> 10:17.834
- But that's what I found.

10:17.965 --> 10:20.489
- Oh, shit. [sighs]

10:22.752 --> 10:26.495
Okay, okay, look.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.149
I'm gonna tell you something.

10:28.279 --> 10:30.194
- Okay.

10:30.325 --> 10:34.024
- There is a substantial...
oh, fuck me.

10:34.155 --> 10:35.939
All right, look.

10:36.070 --> 10:38.855
His only avenue of release
is not through an appeal, okay?

10:38.986 --> 10:40.596
He has another way.

10:40.727 --> 10:43.773
And that way is
$14 million in bearer bonds.

10:43.904 --> 10:45.253
You have to go back out.
You have to find--

10:45.383 --> 10:46.689
- Are you kidding me?

10:46.820 --> 10:48.648
There's 50 cops
out there right now.

10:48.778 --> 10:50.475
As soon as the feds show up,
they're gonna park a goddamn

10:50.606 --> 10:52.303
satellite right above
that property, okay?

10:52.434 --> 10:53.478
You know, it doesn't
fucking matter.

10:53.609 --> 10:55.350
You know what fucking matters?

10:55.480 --> 10:57.744
Your client is gonna be charged
with accessory to capital murder

10:57.874 --> 10:59.789
times twenty-fucking-six.

10:59.920 --> 11:01.486
And then when they're
done with that,

11:01.617 --> 11:02.749
they're gonna charge him
with capital murder

11:02.879 --> 11:05.882
times three
federal fucking agents.

11:06.013 --> 11:08.363
They're gonna be so tired
of charging this motherfucker,

11:08.493 --> 11:10.800
they're gonna forget all about
the kidnapping charges, right?

11:10.931 --> 11:14.282
The guy's done!
Fucking done and so am I!

11:14.412 --> 11:17.807
- My client has been in
prison for nine years, Mike.

11:17.938 --> 11:20.897
How on earth are they gonna
connect him with anything, huh?

11:21.028 --> 11:22.943
I mean, he's in
solitary confinement.

11:23.073 --> 11:25.859
He is allowed one phone call
a week, which is recorded.

11:25.989 --> 11:28.731
He has no computer,
no cell phone, nothing.

11:28.862 --> 11:31.995
- Don't talk to me like
a fucking lawyer, please.

11:32.126 --> 11:33.431
I just talked to
him two days ago.

11:33.562 --> 11:35.346
- Where's the proof
of that, Mike?

11:35.477 --> 11:37.522
I mean, PD certainly
has your phone.

11:37.653 --> 11:39.176
They've already released
your call records.

11:39.307 --> 11:43.398
If they had any--any proof
of--of any connection on that

11:43.528 --> 11:44.965
phone call between you and Milo,

11:45.095 --> 11:46.357
I wouldn't be here
talking to you right now

11:46.488 --> 11:47.794
because I would be at
his arraignment.

11:47.924 --> 11:49.709
They have nothing
and they never will.

11:49.839 --> 11:53.190
- ♪

11:53.321 --> 11:54.365
- I'm being set up.

11:57.760 --> 11:59.196
I'm fucking being set up.

11:59.327 --> 12:00.720
Fucking being set up.

12:00.850 --> 12:03.244
I know it.

12:03.374 --> 12:05.289
If they try to pin me
against the wall for something

12:05.420 --> 12:06.943
that this fucking lunatic has
done, they fucking--

12:07.074 --> 12:09.816
you know what?
I'm not gonna go after Milo.

12:09.946 --> 12:11.774
I'm gonna come
after you, motherfucker.

12:13.515 --> 12:15.125
If I'm gonna go to prison,
it's gonna be for something

12:15.256 --> 12:16.779
I fucking did,
you understand me?

12:16.910 --> 12:18.825
And you have my word
I'm gonna do it to you.

12:18.955 --> 12:20.609
You fucking hear me?

12:20.740 --> 12:22.524
If you don't know what's
really going on right now,

12:22.654 --> 12:25.396
you better figure it the
fuck out, you understand?

12:25.527 --> 12:27.616
And when you do, I'm gonna be
your first fucking phone call.

12:27.747 --> 12:31.098
- Right.
- Yeah. Phone call.

12:31.228 --> 12:34.188
- [pants]

12:34.318 --> 12:38.366
- [pees in fear]

12:53.555 --> 12:56.514
- Aw, damn it.

12:56.645 --> 13:00.127
- [phone ringing]

13:00.257 --> 13:01.955
- [beep]

13:02.085 --> 13:03.652
- Hey, you mind if
I smoke in your car?

13:03.783 --> 13:06.176
- REBECCA: I mean,
I'd rather you didn't.

13:06.307 --> 13:07.787
But if it's been
that kind of day...

13:07.917 --> 13:09.440
- It's been that kind of a day.

13:09.571 --> 13:10.790
- REBECCA: What happened?

13:10.920 --> 13:12.487
- Well, where do I start?

13:12.617 --> 13:14.750
- REBECCA: How
about the beginning?

13:14.881 --> 13:16.012
- I lost in the parent lottery.

13:16.143 --> 13:18.014
And it went
downhill ever since.

13:18.145 --> 13:19.102
- REBECCA: Maybe this
will cheer you up.

13:19.233 --> 13:22.366
I found a new office.
- Yeah, well, it doesn't.

13:22.497 --> 13:24.325
But I'll take it.

13:24.455 --> 13:26.457
- REBECCA: Meet me at the old
office and I'll run you over.

13:26.588 --> 13:28.198
- Yeah, all right.

13:28.329 --> 13:29.417
- [beep]

13:31.767 --> 13:34.988
- [birds chirping]

13:45.476 --> 13:47.174
- [car chiming]

13:51.221 --> 13:52.701
- So you don't smoke
in your car? Is that it?

13:52.832 --> 13:55.486
- Never.

13:55.617 --> 13:57.749
It's my church.

13:57.880 --> 13:59.926
- Well, look, I'll
get it detailed.

14:03.712 --> 14:05.757
- [traffic]

14:05.888 --> 14:07.411
- [bird chirping]

14:07.542 --> 14:09.587
- I think you're really
gonna like the office.

14:09.718 --> 14:11.589
Way less expensive,
which I don't know why,

14:11.720 --> 14:16.029
because it's bigger,
has new carpet, new paint.

14:16.159 --> 14:18.074
- MIKE: Okay.
- REBECCA: It's right here.

14:21.686 --> 14:23.079
What do you think?

14:23.210 --> 14:27.127
- Fuck, Rebecca.
[chuckles]

14:27.257 --> 14:28.998
You know why it's cheap?

14:29.129 --> 14:31.609
It's across the street from
where four murders took place

14:31.740 --> 14:33.785
in three months.

14:33.916 --> 14:36.223
I mean, you--you really
wanna be right here?

14:36.353 --> 14:37.877
Really?

14:38.007 --> 14:39.704
I mean, I was kind of
hoping for a fresh start.

14:39.835 --> 14:42.359
- You want a fresh start, Mike,
we should move to a new city.

14:42.490 --> 14:45.623
They don't have those here.

14:45.754 --> 14:47.451
- [Rebecca opens door]

14:47.582 --> 14:51.151
- [traffic]

15:01.422 --> 15:04.425
- REBECCA: What do you think?

15:04.555 --> 15:08.516
- Yeah. Okay.

15:10.953 --> 15:12.433
- [text chime]

15:15.566 --> 15:17.003
- [sighs]

15:17.133 --> 15:20.658
Fuck, I don't know.

15:20.789 --> 15:22.530
Can we have some new
furniture, at least?

15:22.660 --> 15:24.532
- Not the files.

15:24.662 --> 15:26.055
- Well, yeah, Rebecca,

15:26.186 --> 15:29.058
I think
we should keep the files.

15:29.189 --> 15:30.668
- We should get the
phones and the printers.

15:30.799 --> 15:32.322
I don't see why
we'd buy new ones.

15:32.453 --> 15:36.239
- Yeah, but how about you
and I get new desks...

15:36.370 --> 15:38.067
without fucking blood on it?
How's that?

15:38.198 --> 15:41.984
- New desks, got it.

15:42.115 --> 15:44.204
- [text chime]

15:44.334 --> 15:46.423
- Ed get a hold of you?
He said it was urgent.

15:46.554 --> 15:50.514
- I don't know.
I got nothing.

15:50.645 --> 15:51.863
No, nothing.

15:51.994 --> 15:53.256
You gotta transfer that--
that number on my phone.

15:53.387 --> 15:55.171
- I did.

15:58.566 --> 16:01.047
I need two minutes with this.

16:04.833 --> 16:08.576
- ♪

16:08.706 --> 16:11.144
- [sighs]

